snippet.textDisplay: For those calling this rigged or fixed, think about this for a moment, and I’d love to hear a justification - If this was rigged/fixed, in what universe would the people in power want the fight to end this quickly? It’s actually not good for the sport or for an audience that a fight ends this quick and is this much of a no-contest. Connor haters always come up with some justification, yet they forget the statistics. Connor has an incredibly high K/O ratio. Connor also is explosive and as other fighters have said, he has the best timing and precision of any striker in the sport. You combine this versus an out of prime 38 year old Cowboy, who is typically much slower. The only thing wrong with this fight is that the match up was so incredibly 1-sided, it can be said that it was set-up to get Connor back in the fight game.
